Author: Privatoshi#7913
Content: Someone that gets an F, in English, can't be doing it right---just screwed over by this and that.

Author: Privatoshi#7913
Content:
Lol. Projects get ICO monies. Devs usually get a portion of the supply & they usually mine, which is fair. Centralized exchanges make it out, better than everyone, with listing fees. People very respected in crypto & people with capital, get seed prices and private sales. 
And then average users, we get to gather whatever info we can, and TA, and pay a fee and make a simple trade, hoping we can sell higher.
Then miners. They usually have it tough, especially if they are smaller ones.

That's how I see the landscape
